CHIKUNGUNYA (37): MALAYSIA
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Thu 4 Sep 2008
Source: Malaysian National News Agency (Bernama) [edited]
<http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v3/news.php?id=357178>


A total of 224 people nationwide are suspected to be down with
chikungunya last week [week of 24-30 Aug 2008], compared with only
179 in the previous week.

Health Ministry disease control director Datuk Dr Hasan Abdul Rahman
said 94 cases, or 42 percent of the total were detected by going door-to-door.

The cases this week were reported in 5 states, namely, were Johor,
Melaka, Perak, Penang, and Sarawak, he said in a statement [in Kuala
Lumpur] Thursday [4 Sep 2008].

The total number of cases nationwide is 1703 of which 996 were from
Johor, Melaka (405), Perak (173), Negeri Sembilan (92), Selangor
(26), Pahang (5), Putrajaya (3), Sarawak (2), and Penang (one).

Dr Hasan said chikungunya was a disease [virus] that could only be
spread by the _Aedes_ mosquito.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett

[The chikungunya outbreak has spread widely in peninsular Malaysia
over the past 5 months, and appears to be continuing. ProMED-mail
would appreciate receiving information about vector control efforts
being made there.

A map of Malaysia showing the states can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/malaysia_adm98.jpg>.
- Mod.TY]
